===Etymology===

After Japanese [[petrologist]] Ken-ichi Sugi (1901-1948) in 1976.<ref>Richard V. Gaines, H. Catherine W. Skinner, Eugene E. Foord, Brian Mason, and Abraham Rosenzweig: ''Dana's new mineralogy'', John Wiley & Sons, 1997</ref>

===Noun===
'''sugilite'''

#{{mineralogy}} A [[mineral]] with [[hexagonal]] crystals, often pink or purple but can have different colors, KNa<sub>2</sub>(Fe<sup>+2</sup>,Mn<sup>+2</sup>,Al)<sub>2</sub>Li<sub>3</sub>Si<sub>12</sub>O<sub>30</sub>.

